cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the challenges of segmenting unknown categories and both objects and non-objects, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of attention regions and pointer pixels could also relate to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of convolutional nets is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
